The snake was transferring itself from beneath the boardwalk onto Mangrove trees. I cannot say what it was, except that it was large around and very heavy as we saw the tree branch bend under it's weight. If it was a python I thought to let you know as it was in the midst of a residential area. Sorry this is so late but we only visit Florida for a shore time each year.
